OL,3,CSuspended Reform councillor apologises
OL,4,Cfor alleged racist social media post
OL,6,FA newly elected councillor for Reform
OL,7,FUK has apologised after being accused
OL,8,Fof making racist comments on social
OL,9,Fmedia.
OL,11,FGlenn Gibbins, who was elected to
OL,12,FSunderland City Council last week,
OL,13,Freportedly posted that Nigerians
OL,14,Fshould be used to "fill in pot holes".
OL,16,FCampaign group Hope Not Hate reported
OL,17,Fthe now-deleted post, which is
OL,18,Fbelieved to be from March 2024.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G1/4
